                                Mehaya, Hind and Alqahtani, Imtinan and Alotaibi, Joory},
  book-group-author          = {ACM},
  title                      = {Color-Coded Emotional Learning Serious Games for Children with Autism:
                                Foregrounding Facial Expression Recognition \& Accessibility},
  booktitle                  = {PROCEEDINGS OF THE 22ND INTERNATIONAL WEB FOR ALL CONFERENCE, W4A 2025},
  year                       = {2025},
  pages                      = {25-28},
  note                       = {22nd International Web for All Conference-W4A, Sydney, AUSTRALIA, APR
                                28-29, 2025},
  organization               = {Association for Computing Machinery; Intuit Inc.; ACM SIGCHI; Griffith
                                University},
  abstract                   = {Autism spectrum disorder (ASD) affects one in every thirty-six children
                                worldwide, making it one of the most prevalent cognitive disabilities.
                                Classified as a neurodevelopmental disorder, ASD impairs an individual's
                                ability to recognize and respond to emotions in social interactions.
                                Difficulties in understanding their own emotions or those of others can
                                significantly impact a child's development and communication skills. To
                                address this challenge, the Muheet application introduces a novel
                                approach to emotion perception by leveraging synesthesia, enabling
                                individuals to associate emotions with specific colors. This is achieved
                                through interactive games designed to train the mind in recognizing
                                emotions through logically assigned color associations. Additionally,
                                AI-based facial expression recognition validates this process, ensuring
                                accuracy and engagement. Developed using agile methodology and designed
                                with accessibility guidelines in mind, Muheet ensures inclusivity for
                                all users. A survey conducted to evaluate its effectiveness revealed
                                that 78\% of participants expressed confidence in Muheet's methodology
                                and its potential to improve emotional communication for children with
                                autism.},
